commitResults.messageBody:
If user tries to add the same contact name with different case it
will not be allowed.

If user tries to add a similar contact name (e.g with more spaces),
the new contact will be added but a warning will be shown to inform
them that a similar contact name already exists.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update method in Person and PersonTest

commitResults.messageBody:
Added code to handle duplicate name cases. 

Contact names that are the same but in different case are considered to be the same person. Hence, adding a contact with a name that is the same as existing ones but in different case will raise a CommandException error. (not allowed to add a duplicate contact)

Contact names that are the same but have an extra spacing are considered similar names and the addition of a new contact with similar name will proceed but a warning message will be shown that there are existing contacts with similar names.
